Variation in meristics is presented in
Table 1
. Aspects of coloration and pattern among the type series is notably invariable. Variation does occur in the degree of the development of the black shoulder patch, which gets larger with increasing SVL. It is smallest in the juvenile (SVL 26.7 mm) male from Sungai Sedim ( ZRC 2.6904;
Fig. 3
). The dark shoulder patch is not present in females (
Fig. 3
). Males ZRC 2.6900 and 2.6904 have a light colored vertebral stripe whereas the male holotype ZRC 2.6899 and all the females except ZRC 2.6905 from Pulau Pangkor, Perak lack a vertebral stripe. ZRC 2.6905 also has a darker and more mottled gular region compared to the other specimens in the type series.
